            <h4>Best time to visit</h4>
            <ol>
                <li>1. April is the best time of the year to go to Pasay because of Aliwan Festival, “The Mother of All Fiestas” that features the famous cultural festivals that can be found in the Philippines. Aliwan is a Tagalog word for entertainment or amusement. It is a battle between the best Philippine festivals as the participants dance in a parade with float competitions as well.</li></ol>
            <h4>How to get there:</h4>
            <p>Jeepneys are usually the cheapest and fastest way to get around the city with a trip costing not less than 7-8 Pesos. Taxis are affordable, comfortable and one can get where ever one wants at any time, flag down rates cost P40.</p>
            <h3>Major destinations and cultural festivities</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Resorts World. The fun never stops at Pasay City where the Resorts World Manila is located, with world-class entertainment happening throughout the day, seven days a week.</li>
                <li>2. SM Mall of Asia. The Christmas Sale at SM Mall of Asia (MOA) is attracting international and local tourists. SM Mall of Asia is the 3rd largest shopping mall in Asia and the 4th according to Forbes’ World’s 10 Largest Shopping Malls) largest shopping mall in the world. Every Friday and Saturday at 7pm, a pyromusical event is held in this place. It is a fantastic fireworks display held to music at the SM by the bay behind the mall. In here you can be taken away by the dazzling lights and festive atmo- sphere. Soak in the thrills as you dine and relax in any of the restaurants by the seaside.</li>
